60 2021-01-07 dry mouth I woke up at approximately 4:00 am with an extremely dry mouth. I went into the bathroom and took a ... Read more
Close
I woke up at approximately 4:00 am with an extremely dry mouth. I went into the bathroom and took a drink of water. I returned to bed. I noticed that my breathing was becoming more rapid. I had trouble catching my breath. I sat up on the side of the bed. My heart was pounding and quick. My breathing was difficult. I woke up my wife. After about 5 minutes my symptoms improved. She took my pulse which was now at 62ppm. I laid back down in a reclined position. My symptoms of difficulty breathing and elevated heart rate quickly returned. My pulse was now up to 98 ppm. I sat up again. My symptoms gradually improved. Being unsure of what was going on my wife called 911. The ambulance arrived in about 8 minutes. I was about 60% better. Vitals were improving other than my blood pressure which was 180/100 Being unsure of what was happening, I was transported to Hospital. I had a chest x-ray, a chest CT scan with contrast to rule out a blood clot, blood work including tests to rule out MI x2. All test were negative. By about 6:30 am I was feeling at least 80% better. My breathing I felt had returned to normal. My pulse was down into the 50"s which is my normal range.

60 2021-02-08 dry mouth, dry throat Temporary paralysis of left eyelid which was a symptom of Bells Palsy. At the same time I experien... Read more
Close
Temporary paralysis of left eyelid which was a symptom of Bells Palsy. At the same time I experienced a very disturbing sensation of having no saliva in mouth or throat. I was completely dry and unable to produce saliva. This is my description of the event: I woke up around 3am with rapid heartbeat, lightheadness, and upon opening my eyes I realized my left eyelid was drooping and I was unable to open it. At the same time I experienced extreme dryness in my mouth and throat where i had absolutely no moisture/saliva and was unable to produce any for approximately 20 minutes. I walked to an emergency, which was just 2 blocks away, to get checked out. I told the attending nurse and physician what my symptoms were. Luckily by the time I was admitted to the ER the symptoms began to dissipate. My eyelid was slightly droopy but moving and i was able to produce saliva again. I explained that I've never experienced symptoms like this before in my life and that I believed this was from the vaccine. I had been experiencing symptoms every day since receiving the shot.... from headaches, to fatigue, to tightness in my chest, a cough, pain in my larynx that towards my chest, pain in my upper left abdomen, strange sensations in my legs, brain fogginess, and some swollen lymph nodes.

60 2021-03-24 eye movement disorder Patient received their vaccine and sat in a chair, within approx. two minutes the patient told anoth... Read more
Close
Patient received their vaccine and sat in a chair, within approx. two minutes the patient told another patient they felt hot, I was already walking to the patient to check on them,. The patient's eyes were glazed, Almost immediately the patients eyes rolled back in his head. I shook his arm and shouted to him , he was unresponsive with agonal breaths.. I shouted for help from the other nurses. RNs came immediately. We moved him to the floor, called for an epinephrine injection to be prepared, I began to prepare the site for epinephrine injection to his thigh, nurse checked for pulse... at this time the patient was still unresponsive with agonal breaths... no pulse was felt so compressions were commenced by RN. Nurse gave approx. 15 compressions to the patients chest , the patient spontaneously began to recover. Carotid and radial pulses were felt at this time. Breathing returned to normal. While this was occurring, we called a code blue and 911 was activated. By the time 911 responded the patient was fully conscious , alert and responsive. He could tell us his name and how he felt prior to this incident. The patient was transferred via a stretcher by EMS 911 and RN accompanied him to the ER to give a report. The timeframe for being pulseless and having agonal breaths lasted no more than 30-40 seconds. Patient denied any history of a seizure disorder. No epinephrine or IM Benadryl were administered at the incident site by the responding staff due to the spontaneous recovery.

08:20 am Received 2nd dose of Moderna. Hx of facial swelling to sulfa, so pt was to remain for observation for 30 minutes. At 08:45 am complained of feeling like her eyes were swelling. Pt's daughter was in the car with her and did not notice patient looking any different. No distress noted nor obvious swelling of face, eyes, lips, etc. O2 sat 98% pulse 72. Administered 25 mg benadryl chewable tablet and observed pt for another 30 minutes. At 9:30 am pt reported feeling better, no other problems noted. Pt was discharged to home and told to take benadryl q 6 hrs for the next day and seek emergency care if condition worsened. Call to pt on 03/26/21 revealed that pt had no further problems.
60 2021-03-28 deafness Received the first COVID vaccine on March 18 and two days later I suddenly lost hearing in my left e... Read more
Close
Received the first COVID vaccine on March 18 and two days later I suddenly lost hearing in my left ear. This was near total hearing loss. I could only hear a slight buzz when putting a phone to my ear and listening for the dial tone. Went to my health care provider a couple of days later. They cleaned both ears and examined for any obvious problems. This seemed to improve the hearing in the ear slightly. Physician's Assistant said the hearing loss was most likely a reaction to the vaccine and advised giving it two weeks to see if it improves. Hearing didn't improve much (if at all) throughout the remainder of the week. Over the weekend of March 27-28 hearing seemed to be improving. This morning, March 29, hearing has noticeably improved and I can carry on a phone conversation using my left ear. Hearing is not back to normal yet but it is much better than a few days ago.

60 2021-04-09 blindness loss of sight in his eyes; Soreness around the injection site; This spontaneous case was reported by... Read more
Close
loss of sight in his eyes; Soreness around the injection site; This spontaneous case was reported by a consumer and describes the occurrence of BLINDNESS (loss of sight in his eyes) in a 60-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 028A21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below. The patient's past medical history included No adverse event (No reported medical history). On 30-Mar-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 30-Mar-2021, the patient experienced VACCINATION SITE PAIN (Soreness around the injection site). On 31-Mar-2021, the patient experienced BLINDNESS (loss of sight in his eyes) (seriousness criterion medically significant). At the time of the report, BLINDNESS (loss of sight in his eyes) and VACCINATION SITE PAIN (Soreness around the injection site) outcome was unknown. The action taken with mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) was unknown. Reporter did not allow further contact; Sender's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event of vaccination site pain, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. However,very limited information regarding the event of Blindness has been provided at this time. Further information has been requested.

62 2021-05-13 ringing in ears After my first shot on March 10, I had minor soreness around the injection site and fatigue the day ... Read more
Close
After my first shot on March 10, I had minor soreness around the injection site and fatigue the day following the injection. After my second shot on April 6, I had minor soreness around the injection site, fatigue which lasted two days and low grade fever which I treated with one 400mg dose of ibuprofen. I also developed a persistent high pitch "ringing" in my head/ears. I believe it's what is know as tinnitus. The volume on a range of 1(low) to 10(high) is 2/3 to 5/6. For the first four weeks after my second shot, the ringing was constant and daily. I noticed beginning week 5 that there would be days where it would completely stop or be barely noticeable. The quiet periods ranged from a couple of hours to almost an entire day. The quiet periods are generally begin in the mornings when I first get up. Otherwise they don't appear to follow a pattern. I also noticed, if I consume alcohol it lessens or eliminates the ringing.

The patient then started having chest pain, was short of breath and experienced fatigue. Yesterday (Friday) I felt as if my symptoms (other than residual weakness) were abating, and Friday night I got a full night of unbroken sleep. I awoke on Saturday morning with no symptoms, and felt well enough to challenge myself by attempting my usual 90-minute yoga/stretch workout, which proved to be no problem. Now, at 4 pm on Saturday--about 100 hours after my shot--I feel fairly normal & seem to have no further symptoms. I do plan to lie low & take things easy, and to have as little outside contact as possible between now and my second shot (scheduled for 2/16) in order to minimize the possibility of re-infection.

Close
Took 600mg of Ibuprofen (200mg x3) orally at 7:45AM, 30 minutes later while viewing a medical webinar at my desk at home, I suddenly noticed significant itching of my entire hands which quickly became reddened and progressively swollen as the itching sensation become more generalized within 10-15 minutes. I got up from my chair to go tell my wife but as I walked a few paces, I became extremely weak with visual 'closing in' as I barely prevented myself from collapsing to the floor / losing consciousness. At the same time my tongue was now thickened and malfunctioning making my spoken words to my wife almost unintelligible - all consistent with a CLASSIC ANAPHYLAXIS REACTION. My wife helped me to the couch to recline where I carefully swallowed CHLORPHENIRAMINE 8MG, FAMOTIDINE 20MG; and 15 minutes later DIPHENHYDRAMINE 50MG (I did not have any Epinephrine available from prior 'bee sting kits'). At no time was my breathing impaired nor was there any audible wheezing or dyspnea. After ~45 minutes I was improving noticeably, and after ~2-3 hours I had made a 100% recovery with no sequelae thereafter. Although I had taken my routine morning medications several HOURS PRIOR, nevertheless, (after purchasing several vials of Epinephrine 1mg/1mL for protection in case of another reaction), after this event and over the succeeding days I re-added each of those medications separately / one-at-a-time to ensure that NONE of those was the offending agent - NO problems ensued. For obvious reasons, I have 100% AVOIDED ingesting Ibuprofen or other typical NSAIDs since this episode (although my routine single daily aspirin tablet has presented no problems). BOTTOM LINE: DESPITE HAVING USED IBUPROFEN 400MG OR 600MG PERHAPS 1-2 TIMES WEEKLY AS NEEDED FOR MUSCULOSKELETAL DISCOMFORT OVER MANY YEARS, NEVER UNTIL THIS ANAPHYLACTIC EPISODE 11 DAYS AFTER MY SECOND DOSE OF MODERNA'S COVID-19 VACCINE HAD THERE EVER BEEN ANY TYPE OF ADVERSE REACTION TO IBUPROFEN WHATSOEVER.

Patient received 2nd dose of COVID (Moderna) vaccine on 3/20, and afterwards reported feeling lower back pain, tingling sensations mostly in the lateral thigh down through the lower leg and dorsum of feet. As of one week ago, these symptoms have receded somewhat, and the patient now reports tingling localized to the thigh only, bilaterally, circumferentially. He describes the tingling/numbness as similar to a sunburn, and that it bothers him when walking due to friction between his skin and pant legs. Of note, the patient denies any diplopia, and notes only very minor numbness in the jaw, both of which he has experienced during episodes of his postviral reaction. Furthermore, patient did report a worsening of his tinnitus, but states that it has improved in the past 3-4 days, almost back to baseline. Patient was taking 3x 200 mg ibuprofen to little effect, and reported similar lack of relief with naproxen. Patient notes inconsistent use of B12 supplements. Diagnosis: Immune/inflammatory response to COVID vaccine. This is the most likely etiology of the patient's symptoms given the timing of events and his history of postviral herpetic reactions. His symptoms of tingling/numbness began soon after his 2nd dose of the COVID vaccine, and due to this rapid onset and temporal association, it appears likely that his current symptoms may be related. While the symptoms described by the patient and their duration are not typical of COVID vaccine side effects, these neurological symptoms are similar to previous episodes (albeit in a different location) experienced by the patient, which responded to antivirals. As the COVID vaccine is immunogenic, and given these prior episodes of similar symptoms, the patient's current presentation is likely a reaction to the vaccine.

At the time of the report, COVID-19 (COVID-19/ tested positive for Covid-19), AGEUSIA (loss of taste), ANOSMIA (loss of smell), DECREASED APPETITE (loss of appetite), URINARY INCONTINENCE (loss control of bladder), ASTHENIA (extreme weakness), BLOOD GLUCOSE DECREASED (Blood sugar decreased), DIARRHOEA (Diarrhea), VOMITING (Vomiting), NAUSEA (Nausea) and FATIGUE (fatigue/ tiredness) outcome was unknown. Close
Loss of hearing in his right ear; A spontaneous report was received from a 73-year-old, male, patient who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced hearing loss in right ear. The patient's medical history, as provided by the reporter, included ventriculoperitoneal (VP) shunt in his head. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On 12 Jan 2021, approximately two days prior to the onset of the event, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 14 Jan 2021, the patient had dental work done where four crowns were prepped and temporaries were put in, he then lost hearing in his right ear. Treatment information was not provided. He thinks that the loss of hearing might be due to this dental procedure as they were drilling for hours. He states that he has a VP shunt in this head which needs readjustments occasionally. He is seeing his neurosurgeon for the readjustment. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the event was not reported. The outcome of the event, hearing loss in right ear, was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 73 year-old, male patient with history of ventriculoperitoneal (VP) shunt in his head, who experienced event of hearing loss in right ear. The event occurred 2 days after the first and last dose of mRNA-1273 vaccine administration. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded and the event is assessed as possibly related. However, on the same day and prior to the onset of the event, the patient had extensive dental procedures done which may provide an alternative explanation for the event.

Occlusion on right eye; Can't see out of his right eye; hemorrhage in right eye; Case reference number MOD-2021-012734 is a spontaneous case report sent by a Non-Healthcare Professional on 09-FEB-2021, which refers to a male patient who received the first dose of Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced occlusion of the right eye and blindness in the right eye which required hospitalization and the event of hemorrhage in the right eye. The patient's medical history included a shunt installation for hydrocephalus. The patient's medication history included amoxicillin, omeprazole, potassium citrate, sertraline hydrochloride, tamsulosin, amoxicillin trihydrate, benzydamine hydrochloride, bromhexine hydrochloride, trospium and unspecified sinus medications. On 15JAN2021, the patient received the first dose of Moderna COVID-19 (mRNA-1273) Vaccine (Lot: 041L20A) intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 17JAN2021, the patient's wife reported that the patient couldn't see out of his right eye. He went to the emergency room and his ophthalmologist reported that the patient had an occlusion on the right eye which was not a result of the vaccine. On 19JAN2021, the patient left the hospital. Later that same week, the patient visited another ophthalmologist that observed a hemorrhage on his right eye with an unknown etiology. On 04FEB2021, the patient went to the dentist where multiple infections and molars were identified. Treatment included amoxicillin 875mg for 10 days. Action taken for the events of occlusion of the right eye, blindness in the right eye and hemorrhage in the right eye associated with mRNA-1273 was not reported. The outcome of the events was unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 73-year-old male patient, who experienced a serious unexpected events of vascular occlusion, blindness, and eye hemorrhage, after receiving first dose of mRNA-1273 (lot # 041L20A). Very limited information regarding this event has been provided at this time. Further information has been requested.

73 2021-03-14 pain in jaw Received the vaccine on Thursday 3/11 3:15PM. Around 2PM on Friday 3/12, noticed that my right jaw ... Read more
Close
Received the vaccine on Thursday 3/11 3:15PM. Around 2PM on Friday 3/12, noticed that my right jaw was feeling sore when I chewed on things. Didn't think much of it until dinner time when my jaw hurt everytime I took a bite of food. Couldn't think of anything I did to cause it, and assumed it would get better soon. On Saturday, my jaw was still sore when I had lunch, but maybe a little better. But then at dinner time it was back to hurting again. Sunday it was still sore when I had lunch. By then I was starting to attribute it to possibly being the vaccine I received on 3/11, even though there was no mention of this as a side effect on any of the sheets I received when I got my vaccine. I then signed-up to v-safe to see what they might offer. Then I called the on-call nurseline (where I got the shot). An RN called back and we went over everything, and at the end she recommended I go into an Emergency room to get checked out because jaw paint can possibly mean heart issues or other things to be concerned about. I was very surprised about her recommendation, but decided to take her advice. Went to an emergency clinic. While I was in the waiting room, a woman who was also waiting said she heard me talking about the reason I was in and said her husband had experienced the same symptoms after his Covid vaccine that I did! He had a Moderna shot on 2/27 and then several days later his right jaw got sore. He went to the doctor on 3/8 and they said he had TMJ, but the next day his pain went away and he has been ok since. They examined me, took blood for Troponin, did an EKG. All looked OK. I told them about the person in the waiting room and her husband and they said they weren't aware that this was an issue with this vaccine. They sent me home and said to monitor and follow-up with my family doctor if it persists. As of today, I am still having the pain in my right jaw. It has stayed the same since it started - no better/no worse. I suspect of there are 2 of us with this symptom, there are probably many others.

He spit up a lot of thick phlegm (which can be normal for him, due to IBM). After 15 mins, the sweat and shaking died down, and he felt better enough to think about going to sleep. But 5 minutes later, the nausea returned, and he threw up about 25 mL of black "coffee grounds-like" fluid. (The smell was HORRIBLE). After getting through with that (about 15 minutes), he wretched up more thick mucus with a few flecks of black cells in it. After awhile, he felt okay enough to go back to sleep. He felt weak and horrible and was shaking. At the recommendation of the advice nurse, he was taken to the ER by ambulance. Upon arriving, he waited around an hour for an ER bed. They put him on an IV, did a physical inspection and did blood work. His sodium was a bit low, but in normal range. Potassium levels were fine. He was mentally clear the whole time, but physically very weak. He was kept overnight after a hemochrit test in the afternoon showed low levels of hemoglobin. He was meant to get an endoscopy, but they decided to allow him to eat and sent him home after noon bc they hadn't yet been able to schedule him for it and he was in pain and massively hungry. When he got home, he still barely ate, and still isn't eating almost anything a day later. His stool was incredibly black and thick and SMELLY immediately upon arriving home (he had not defecated for 48 hours at that point), and he has not been able to defecate since, which is extremely abnormal (he usually goes each day in the morning upon waking). They believe that he may have bleeding in his stomach or upper GI or esophagus, but we are waiting for an endoscopy later this week. He is still very weak and frail and fatigued.

Double vision; Chills; Low graded fever (99.8); A spontaneous report was received from a consumer, concerning a 75-year-old male patient, who received Moderna's COVID-19 Vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced double vision, chills and low graded fever (99.8). The patient's medical history was not provided. Concomitant product use was not provided by the reporter. On 30 JAN 2021, the patient received their second of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (Batch number 012M20A) intramuscularly for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 31JAN2021, after the vaccine administration, the patient developed chills and low-grade fever of 99.8, hence he was given with acetaminophen to alleviate these symptoms. On 01 FEB 2021, the patient started experiencing double vision, hence, on 05 FEB 2021, the patient went to their eye doctor who instructed the patient to go to the emergency room (ER). The ER doctor admitted the patient to the hospital to run some tests and labs. The patient was tested for stroke, tumor, and bell palsy and all these tests were negative. The hospital conducted several CT and MRI and they were all negative. The neurologists did not know what was going on with the patient. Hence, he was discharged from the hospital on 07 FEB 2021. The patient was still having symptoms. Treatment information was not provided. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events were not applicable. The outcome of the events double vision, chills and low graded fever (99.8) were considered not resolved at the time of this report.; Reporter's Comments: Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Further information has been requested.

No longer has vision in that eye; Stroke; Sneezing; A spontaneous report was received from a consumer concerning a 75-years-old, male patient who experienced stroke, lost vision in one eye and Sneezing. The patient's medical history was not provided. Products known to have been used by the patient, within two weeks prior to the event, included blood pressure medicines. On 31 Dec 2020, approximately one day prior to the onset of the symptoms, the patient received their first of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 [Lot number 039K20A] intramuscularly in the left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 01 Jan 2021, the patient reported sneezing and had vision issues. He was told that it appeared he had a stroke. Treatment for the event included eye drops. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events was not provided. The outcome of the events stroke, lost vision in one eye and Sneezing were unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 75 year old, male patient, who experienced a serious unexpected event of blindness and cerebrovascular accident. Concomitant medication included blood pressure medication. Very limited information regarding this event has been provided at this time. Further information has been requested.
